There are multiple ways to define "omnipotence." Many human scriptures from different religions, cults, sects, etc. make liberal use of terms in many different languages, and then a thousand years and fifteen "translations" later someone is left attempting to interpret "original meaning."

Omnipotence, according to the ability of humans to conceive of it in the Late Stone Age as it transitioned into the Early Bronze Age, is radically different than it's conception during the Iron Age, and is evolving at non-linear speeds in the modern Silicon and Quantum Ages at rates that couldn't even be imagined 50 years ago.

Humanity's grasp of just how big Infinity is, and how Infinity is configured, was largely unimagined 30 to 40 years ago. 20 or 30 years from today our current understanding will be obsolete and somewhat quaint.

"Omnipotence" has a vastly different meaning today than it has ever had in the past. Just because the word seems to be the same, they way a person was using it a hundred or a thousand or ten thousand years ago doesn't mean it had the same meaning or intention as it would in today's context.

God could have All the Knowledge of Everything at this moment in time and All Time before Now, and that would be one interpretation of omnipotence. It might not necessarily mean He has All Knowledge for All Time after Now. He may have superior predictive ability and make really good guesses, while at the same time being very curious as to what exactly will happen and enjoy watching it as it plays out.

Relative to Humans, that would be omnipotence, and still accommodate various scriptures in which God doesn't seem to have known exactly what would happen until after it did. There's an enormous amount of shit that's happened in the last 1000 years that God should have known would happen and should have mentioned if He had known about it.

But, nothing.

>yet though hearing that makes me question why
TV anime has a lot more restrictions over what can be told, and shown than manga, If a manga with that kind of content is getting a TV anime adaption, it has to toned down for TV standards. Hell, even shonen, which is the bread and butter of the anime industry, gets heavily toned down in their Television releases.

The only ways to circunvent that is to make an OVA, since it is made directly for home video format, but it is also financially riskier to do that.

Or to make no anime at all, and not release a bogged down version of the original work.
